      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KAPAKIRI (1) has settled back in the field and failed to launch a serious challenge in his two runs this time in work. Strips fitter and looks well treated after the claim for the in-form Siena Grima. Meets a plain bunch today so watch for a return to form. COVERT THINKING (5) hasn't landed a blow in three runs this prep, the latest over 1550m here a fortnight ago. Bred to want a bit of ground so getting beyond the mile for the first time might see a spike in form. ALLEGRO MISS (2) came from last on the turn to get up for third recently in a similar race here. In-form mare suited by the small field. Should be closing strongly again. VELARIS (6) finished third here at this trip two back then struggled in Saturday company last start. Can turn things around in this more suitable contest. FAY'S ANGELS (4) should be ready to find peak form at the fourth run back.",
